<item>
            <title>[LU-37] Builds failing on Ubuntu 2.6.32 due to removal of bdi.wb_cnt</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-37</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to Hudson &lt;a href=&quot;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b1_8-client-ubuntu/lastFailedBuild/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b1_8-client-ubuntu/lastFailedBuild/&lt;/a&gt; (#112) b1_8 build is failing because of wb_cnt has been removed since 2.6.34 from the kernel, and this must have been back-ported to Ubuntu.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see in master that bugzilla bug 23064 (commit e218d06f97d0c3bb8ddba68060320a1ff45984b8) landed a better patch for the &quot;new backing_dev_info&quot; change than b1_8 bug 23118 (commit 55b8f0d30b1c3e10fae024f78eb04dde74b34bf7).&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>Ubuntu 2.6.32 kernel build with b1_8</environment>
